C:\Users\Admin\eclipse-workspace --> Workspace location.
C:\Users\Admin\eclipse-workspace\Selenium --> project location
Pre-Requisite: Git should be installed on the system.
Go to local project location and open git bash here and enter command --> git init
C:/Users/Admin/eclipse-workspace/Selenium/.git/
git config --global user.name "Eknath"  --> One time
git config --global user.email "eknathmarathe1993@gmail.com"  --> One time
git add .  --> This will add all files to staging area.
git commit -m "My First Commit"  --> This will commit all added files to the local repository
git status
Now login/signup to github and create a repository on gihub with same name as the project name on local.
Copy the remote repository url e.g. https://github.com/eknathm/Selenium.git from github application.
Connect local repository with Remote repository by below onetime command.
git remote add origin "https://github.com/eknathm/Selenium.git" --> One time command.
git push origin master
After entering above command it the popup will be visible asking for cred/token.
Create a token on github: Profile --> Settings --> Developer Settings --> Personal access tokens --> Tokens(classic) 
--> Generate new token(classic) --> select admin, repo access
Provide Username as github username and password as above generated token.
e.g. Token = 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
Note: If token is expired you can create new one and use directly.
********************************************************************************************
Round 2: 
Update and add files.
git add .
git commit -m "Second commit"
git push oriogin master

Pull the files from remote repository:
git pull "https://github.com/eknathm/Selenium.git"
